name: Randevu Cafe
address: Jl. Pantai Kedungu No.1, Nyitdah, Kec. Kediri, Kabupaten Tabanan, Bali 82121, Indonesia
review 1: I just dont understand, why even at night this cafe feels sooo hot, like a sauna. The food is okay, the service is absolutely on point. Please fix your ac, thank u
review 2: Steak was like a rubber sole, very dry and not fresh. Dim sam was not fresh too
review 3: I ordered via Gojek, restaurant confirmed my order but when the gojek arrived the restaurant was closed!
review 4: The Taro drink is incredible, must have
review 5: nice little cafe, cheap prices and tasted good

name: 4T Homemade Pizza
address: C4C5+RJQ, Jl. Pantai Kedungu, Pejaten, Kec. Kediri, Kabupaten Tabanan, Bali 82121, Indonesia
review 1:
Delicious Pizza and Cookies! Will keep coming back for more.. we enjoyed the pizza so much, it taste great and they‚Äôre very generous with the portion, we couldnt even finish What we ordered.
We also love the fresh baked Cookies. Everything that we tried from this place were delicious and fresh and the place has nice homey feel to it and good vibe, it felt like eating at my own home‚Ä¶
Must try!
review 2:
Everything is Enak!
Beyond your expectation. They also have sushi, and pasta!
Place has character for sure. Owned and cooked by friendly old couple.
Ibuk has super nice smile, bapak has cool long dreadlock hair. They both have nice taste of music you can hear in the evening from this warung..
review 3: Just found hidden gem home made pizza in pejaten closed to tanah lot & kedungu. Takeaway chicken pizza and cupcakes (chocolate & banana).
review 4: This pizza place feels like home! The pizza tastes amazing, with the owner pak wayan making everything himself, and the owners are so warm and friendly. My favourite place in Pejaten.
review 5: Great pizza, low price and homey ambience

review 4: Great and humble driver tourism in bali.
